caption: One profile, multiple inputs
tags: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/recipes
title: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/recipes/multiple-inputs
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Same schema, different sources.  The ''Example Moodle Forum'' profile works
on both ''Example Moodle Forum Data'' and the noisy
''Moodle Forum Data (with junk)'' fixture — the tolerant parser handles the
extra wrapping in the latter.

For your own:

* Hand-write a profile that uses only the fields the inputs have in common.
* Run multiple Converts against it with different paste-ins.  Each Convert is independent; previous Applies don't interfere unless titles collide.
